Creates a new soy renderer.
An interface for a supplier that provides Soy injected data.
Type definition for strict Soy templates. Very useful when passing a template as an argument.

Converts a processed Soy template into a single node. If the rendered HTML string represents a single node, then that node is returned. Otherwise, a DIV element is returned containing the rendered nodes.
The processed template of kind HTML or TEXT (which will be escaped).
The DOM helper used to create DOM nodes; defaults to goog.dom.getDomHelper.
Rendered template contents, wrapped in a parent DIV element if necessary.

Renders a Soy template into a single node or a document fragment. If the rendered HTML string represents a single node, then that node is returned (note that this is not a fragment, despite them name of the method). Otherwise a document fragment is returned containing the rendered nodes.

The data for the template.
The injected data for the template.

The resulting node or document fragment.

Renders a Soy template and then set the output string as the innerHTML of an element. It is recommended to use this helper function instead of directly setting innerHTML in your hand-written code, so that it will be easier to audit the code for cross-site scripting vulnerabilities.
The element whose content we are rendering into.
The Soy template defining the element's content.
The data for the template.
The injected data for the template.

Sets the processed template as the innerHTML of an element. It is recommended to use this helper function instead of directly setting innerHTML in your hand-written code, so that it will be easier to audit the code for cross-site scripting vulnerabilities.
The element whose content we are rendering into.
The processed template of kind HTML or TEXT (which will be escaped).

Whether to require all Soy templates to be "strict html". Soy templates that use strict autoescaping forbid noAutoescape along with many dangerous directives, and return a runtime type SanitizedContent that marks them as safe.

If this flag is enabled, Soy templates will fail to render if a template returns plain text -- indicating it is a non-strict template.
